---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

const article = { author: "Maine Dispensary Guide Editorial Team", publishDate: "2026-01-10", modifiedDate: "2026-03-15", section: "Compliance & Legal" };
---

<Layout 
  title="Maine Cannabis Regulations | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Complete guide to Maine cannabis regulations and legal framework. Stay compliant with OCP rules, local ordinances, and state laws governing adult-use dispensaries."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507090960745-b32f65d3113a?q=80&w=1200&h=400&auto=format&fit=crop"
  article={article}
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Cannabis Regulations in Maine</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Understanding the legal framework for operating a dispensary in Maine</p>
    </div>

    <Callout title="Compliance as a Foundation" type="tip">
      Navigating regulations isn't just about following rules; it's about building a business that the community can trust. When you embrace compliance as a core value, you're protecting your dream and ensuring that the Maine cannabis industry remains a leader in safety and professionalism. We're all in this together!
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>State Regulatory Framework</h2>
      <p>Maine's cannabis industry is regulated by the <a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a>, which oversees licensing, compliance, and enforcement for both medical and <a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/adult-use" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">adult-use</a> cannabis businesses.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Regulations</h2>
      <p>The <a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">OCP Rules and Statutes</a> provide the comprehensive legal framework for all operations.</p>
      
      <h3>Licensing Requirements</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Completed Maine OCP adult-use retail license application</li>
        <li>Local municipal approval and zoning compliance</li>
        <li>Secure retail location meeting 500ft school buffer</li>
        <li>Metrc seed-to-sale tracking system setup</li>
        <li>Timely license renewal</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">OCP Rules & Statutes</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal or financial advice. Cannabis regulations are subject to change; always consult with the Maine Office of Cannabis Policy and qualified legal counsel.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2 { margin-top: 0; }
  section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
</style>
